4 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Condition of grants -- disbursement of funds. (1) The disbursement of
5 grant funds for the projects chosen by the department of commerce pursuant to [section 3] is subject to the
6 following conditions:
7 (a) for grants in an amount of $25,000 or more, the grant recipient shall document the availability
8 of matching funds or in-kind contribution of assets with an appraised value from private sources representing at
9 least $1 in value for each $5 of the grant;
10 (b) the grant recipient shall execute a grant agreement with the department of commerce that
11 includes a project management plan and reporting requirements to track the outcomes of allocated grants; and
12 (c) the grant recipient shall satisfy other specific requirements considered necessary by the
13 department of commerce to accomplish the purpose of the project as evidenced by the application to the
14 department of commerce.
15 (2) Projects must adhere to the design standards required by applicable regulations. Recipients of
16 program funds for projects that are not subject to any design standards must comply with generally accepted
17 industry standards.
18 (3) If actual project expenses are lower than the projected expense of the project, the department
19 of commerce shall reduce the amount of grant funds to be provided to grant recipients.
20
21 NEW SECTION. Section 6. Maximum state funding available -- for each project -- for each
22 county. (1) The amount of state funding allocated to entities within an individual county under [sections 3
23 through 5] may not exceed $1 million. No more than two applications may be funded in any one county.
24 (2) The amount of a grant to a single project may not exceed $500,000.
25
